The Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Kakanfo Inn and Conference, Ibadan, Mr Damola Are, has urged the government at all levels to improve on security in the country and address infrastructural deficit attract more investments. Are said this while speaking with journalists at the New Year party and award ceremony for staff of the hotel in Ibadan, Oyo State. He said the harsh business environment should be looked into in order to make the country investment-friendly. According to him, investors will not put their funds where there is no security. Are said, “Government should create an enabling environment. There should be quality facilities in place; there should be a
modern transportation system and adequate security. “Government should create more tax shelters for hospitality companies to spur growth, which, in turn, will benefit the overall economy.” Earlier, more than a dozen outstanding staff of the Kakanfo Inn and Conference Centre were rewarded with cash gifts by the management of the hotel. Are said the objective of the event was to “appreciate and recognise last year’s top performers and motivate the entire team forward as we go into 2022”. “My advice for them is to create a solid and memorable customer experience, exhibit integrity and always maintain a positive character,” he said. Among the recipients of the awards are the Head of Club XS, Deji Aboderin; the Human Resources Manager of the hotel, Bukola Odafe-Fakeye; and Nkwoye Kelachukwu, who emerged the most valuable transport and security team member for 2021. Other winners are Sola Makinde, Owolabi Adegoke, Felix Umoren, Ayomide Afolabi, Ndem Onyebuchi, Haruna Sunday, Dennis Williams and Marvelous Adadu. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com